# Securelic Vulnerability Scanners List

A comprehensive list of security scanners and tools provided by [Securelic](https://securelic.com) for securing networks, servers, web applications, and APIs.
## Overview

Securelic is an open-source powered vulnerability scanner designed to help organizations discover their attack surface, scan for CVEs, and manage security risks through automated workflows.

## Scanners & Features

| Scanner Name | Description | Key Features |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Attack Surface Discovery** | Continuously maps external footprints. | Subdomain identification, live service detection, open port mapping, and technology fingerprinting. |
| **Network & Infrastructure Scanner** | Scans servers and network assets for weaknesses. | Multi-layer scanning, detection of misconfigurations, and identification of outdated components. |
| **Web Application Scanner (DAST)** | Automated penetration testing for modern web apps. | Detects injection flaws, broken authentication, insecure redirects, and XSS. |
| **API Security Scanner** | Specialized testing for REST and GraphQL APIs. | Analysis of API endpoints, validation of input fields, and detection of logical vulnerabilities. |
| **CVE & Vulnerability Engine** | Deep engine for identifying known exposures. | Scans for critical CVEs, runtime flaws, and zero-day exposures using updated databases. |
| **SSL/TLS & Certificate Analyzer** | Evaluates the health of cryptographic setups. | Certificate expiration tracking, protocol version checks (TLS 1.2/1.3), and cipher strength analysis. |
| **Compliance Validator** | Maps findings to global security standards. | Provides insights aligned with GDPR, HIPAA, PCI DSS, and ISO 27001. |
| **Continuous Pentesting** | Automated and ongoing security validation. | Integration with DevSecOps, real-time threat monitoring, and automated regression testing. |

## Technical Capabilities

* **Advanced Fingerprinting:** Identifies tech stacks and service versions automatically.
* **Actionable Reporting:** Generates detailed reports with risk prioritization and remediation guidance.
* **Real-time Monitoring:** Continuously tracks infrastructure changes and security header regressions.
* **Open Source Core:** Powered by industry-standard open-source security engines.

## Integration & Deployment

Securelic is designed to fit into modern development pipelines:

* **SaaS / Cloud-native:** No complex on-premise setup required.
* **DevSecOps Ready:** Automated triggers for continuous security.

